SIMPLE: indite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indite
<hw>In*dite"</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n*d⟦imac⟧t")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Indited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Inditing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>enditen</ets> to indite, indict, OF. <ets>enditer</ets> to
indicate, show, dictate, write, inform, and <ets>endicter</ets> to
accuse; both fr. LL. <ets>indictare</ets> to show, to accuse, fr. L.
<ets>indicere</ets> to proclaim, announce; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in +
<ets>dicere</ets> to say. The word was influenced also by L.
<ets>indicare</ets> to indicate, and by <ets>dictare</ets> to dictate.
See <er>Diction</er>, and cf. <er>Indict</er>, <er>Indicate</er>,
<er>Dictate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To compose; to write; to be author of; to dictate;
to prompt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My heart is <qex>inditing</qex> a good matter.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
xlv. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Could a common grief have <qex>indited</qex> such expressions?</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hear how learned Greece her useful rules <qex>indites</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To invite or ask.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She will <qex>indite</qex> him to some supper.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To indict; to accuse; to censure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Indite
<hw>In*dite"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To compose; to write, as a
poem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wounded I sing, tormented I <qex>indite</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inditement</ent>⟦br⟧
